George Odiwuor @PeopleDailyKe Homa Bay County Assembly Deputy Chief Sergeant-At-Arms Idah Adhiambo was yesterday charged with stealing the Assembly’s mace. She was accused of stealing the mace valued at Sh800,000 from the Assembly on October 28 with an alternative charge of handling stolen goods. Adhiambo was accused of stealing the mace for the benefit of Assembly Speaker Elizabeth Ayoo knowing or having reason to believe it to be stolen property. Appearing before Principal Magistrate Susan Ndegwa, she pleaded not guilty and was released on a Sh200,000 bond and a surety of a similar amount. The case will be mentioned on November 12 pending hearing on November 26.